## 3. What this changes in your registry schema

Add two fields to the connector object from `01_CORE_ARCHITECTURE.md §3`:

```json
{
  "connector_id": "canva",
  "feasibility": "self_serve",
  "tos_risk": false,
  ...
}
{
  "connector_id": "whatsapp_personal",
  "feasibility": "accessibility_only",
  "tos_risk": true,
  "risk_note": "Personal-account automation; keep to single-message, user-initiated actions only. Never batch or schedule sends."
}
```

**Gate logic addition:** if `tos_risk: true`, the plan-execute-verify loop (§4 of core doc) requires an explicit user confirmation step before execution, not just before the app is connected — surfaced once per session, not once per action (avoid alert fatigue, but don't let it fire silently either).

