## 4. How Claude's own connector directory answers your "1,000,000 apps" question

Recap of the verified pattern (already found last session, restated because it directly shapes your UI): Claude doesn't try to pre-build every app. It ships a **curated directory** (named partners like Figma, Canva, Asana, Slack, Adobe, monday.com) plus a **generic custom-connector escape hatch** — a technical user can paste an API base URL + key for anything not in the directory. Auth flows through OAuth so the model never sees a password, and access is scoped to what the user's own account can already do.

**Direct translation to your connector picker UI:** ship Tier A apps as one-tap "Connect" buttons (pre-built OAuth flows you own). Ship a separate "Add custom connector" flow for power users — paste a base URL + API key — rather than promising to pre-build every service that exists. This is the only version of "1,000,000 apps" that's honest to build toward: you don't build 1,000,000 integrations, you build one generic mechanism plus a growing curated list.

